White Box - CAN see code
Black Box - CANT see code
Unit Testing - Testing itself alone
Integration Testing - Testing how it fits in
Security - Security Testing

Valid - Correct Data that SHOULD go there
Invalid - Incorrect Data that SHOULDNT go there (however it is of the same data type - string, int, etc.)
Erroneous - Completely incorrect data of the wrong data type (e.g: "Name: ';';12;12';2'3")
Extreme - Just Inside/Outside possible bounds 

E.G: Password - Max 12 Char - No ; Allowed

Valid - Password1!
Invalid - PasswordPassword (Too Long)
Extreme Valid - Password123! (Exactly 12 character maximum)
Extreme Invalid - Password1234! (1 character off of maximum)
Erroneous - ;;;;;;; (Blatantly invalid and the wrong data type)
